The paper deals with a problem in computational geometry involving the labeling of points on the boundary of a rectangle with axis-aligned curves. This falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG). The algorithms presented in the paper involve the use of data structures (cs.DS) and graph theory (cs.DM, cs.GT) to solve the problem. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of logarithmic time in one of the algorithms, which suggests the possibility of some form of optimization or algorithmic analysis (cs.SI).
